wikipedia_page.main: Angela Barnwell (11 January 1936 – 29 June 1965) was a British swimmer. She competed in two events at the 1952 Summer Olympics. She won the 1952 ASA National Championship 100 metres freestyle title.She died from cancer, aged 29.
